@startuml 04_websocket_lifecycle
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Arial

title WebSocket Connection Lifecycle

actor "Client" as Client
participant "WS Handler" as WS
participant "Auth Middleware" as Auth
participant "WebSocket Hub" as Hub
participant "Redis\n(Leaderboard)" as Redis
participant "Redis\n(Pub/Sub)" as PubSub

== Connection Establishment ==

Client -> WS : HTTP Upgrade\nGET /ws/scoreboard?token=<JWT>
WS -> Auth : Validate JWT from query param / header
Auth --> WS : user_id (or 401 → close)
WS -> Hub : Register(conn, user_id)
Hub -> Redis : ZREVRANGE leaderboard 0 9 WITHSCORES
Redis --> Hub : top10[]
Hub -> Client : [WS] scoreboard:init\n{ top10[] }

== Heartbeat (Keepalive) ==

loop Every 30 seconds
  Hub -> Client : PING frame
  Client -> Hub : PONG frame
end

== Score Update Broadcast (triggered by Score Service) ==

note over PubSub : Score Service publishes\nafter successful update
PubSub -> Hub : scoreboard:update message\n{ top10[] }
Hub -> Client : [WS] scoreboard:update\n{ top10[] }
note right of Hub
  Broadcast to ALL
  registered connections
  on this server instance
end note

== Idle Timeout ==

Hub -> Hub : No PONG received\nfor > 60s
Hub -> Client : Close frame (code 1000)
Hub -> Hub : Deregister(conn)

== Client Reconnect Strategy ==

Client -> Client : Detect close / error
Client -> Client : Wait: 1s → 2s → 4s ... max 30s\n(exponential backoff)
Client -> WS : Reconnect with fresh JWT

== Token Expiry During Session ==

Hub -> Hub : Detect JWT exp < now()
Hub -> Client : Close frame (code 4001 — token expired)
Client -> Client : Obtain fresh token from Auth Service
Client -> WS : Reconnect with new JWT

@enduml
